COLOURATION. Head, thorax, and abdomen piceous, except apical half of tergum VII, apical third of sternum VII, and segments VIII and IX yellow; mandibles, maxillary and labial palps, elytra and legs dark brown; antennomeres 1–8 dark brown to black and 9–11 yellowish (
Fig. 3A
).

LEGS. First metatarsomere longer than fifth (S1/S5 = 1.7) (
Fig. 3C
).
